---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const principles = [
  { name: 'Sensible prices, published', desc: 'No enterprise mark-up, no "let\'s get you on a call" before we\'ll say a number. Our prices are on the website.' },
  { name: 'A human in the loop, always', desc: 'Agents do the work; Waseem makes the decisions and takes the calls. We promise a meeting within one week of first contact.' },
  { name: 'Built properly, not prototyped', desc: 'Audited, monitored, backed up, tested. The same standard we hold our own infrastructure to.' },
  { name: 'Governed, staged delivery', desc: 'You see it working before it goes live. No big-bang launches, no nasty surprises.' },
  { name: 'Remote-first, Bradford-rooted', desc: 'Based in Bradford, serving Leeds, Manchester and the UK. Where you are is not a problem we\'ve ever had.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="An AI-run consultancy with a human at the helm. Automancer's finance, project tracking and website run on agents — every decision and every call run by Waseem Ilyas, in Bradford."
>
  <section class="page-hero hatch">
    <div class="page-hero__glow" aria-hidden="true" data-px="26"></div>
    <div class="page-hero__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">About Automancer</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">An AI-run business, with a human at the helm.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        Most consultancies talk about AI. Automancer is one. The finance, the project tracking, the
        website you're reading — all run by agents. Every decision and every call — run by Waseem.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Automancer -->
  <section class="section on-near">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="story">
        <div class="story__aside"><span class="story__tag">01 · the name</span><h2>Why "Automancer"?</h2></div>
        <div class="story__body">
          <p>
            An automancer works magic through machines. That's the joke, and it's also the honest job
            description. We make small businesses run like they're enchanted — admin that does itself,
            systems that talk to each other, work that just quietly happens overnight — and then we tell
            you plainly that it isn't magic at all. It's very good engineering, pointed at the boring
            problems that cost you the most.
          </p>
          <p>
            Small businesses have been priced out of proper automation for years. The good stuff went to
            companies with six-figure budgets and an IT department; everyone else got a shelf of apps that
            don't quite fit and a spreadsheet holding it all together. We think that's daft. The technology
            to fix it is here, it's cheaper than ever, and there's no reason a care provider in Bradford or
            a manufacturer in Manchester shouldn't have systems as sharp as anyone's.
          </p>
          <p>So we built a consultancy to prove it — by running the consultancy itself on exactly the tools we sell.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The business is the demo -->
  <section class="section on-paper">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="story">
        <div class="story__aside"><span class="story__tag">02 · the demo</span><h2>The business is the demo.</h2></div>
        <div class="story__body">
          <p>Here's the part other firms won't show you: how we actually run.</p>
          <p>
            Automancer's own back office is run by AI agents. They handle the finance operations —
            invoicing, reconciliation, the bookkeeping grind. They track every project, lane by lane, and
            flag anything that needs a human before it moves. They wrote and maintain this website. They
            write the field notes on it. They work through the night without complaint or overtime.
          </p>
          <p>
            And then there's the line we will never cross: <strong>a human makes every decision and takes
            every call.</strong> That human is Waseem. The agents draft, calculate, monitor and propose.
            Waseem decides. Every invoice that goes out, every recommendation that reaches you, every
            judgement call — a person made it, on purpose. The agents are the hands. The head stays human.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're this open about it for two reasons. One, honesty: you deserve to know what's automated
            and what isn't. Two, it <em>is</em> the pitch — if we can run a whole consultancy this way, we
            can absolutely take the weight off your business. We're not experimenting on you. We already
            ran the experiment on ourselves.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Waseem -->
  <section class="section on-dark hatch">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="story">
        <div class="story__aside"><span class="story__tag">03 · the human</span><h2>Meet Waseem.</h2></div>
        <div class="story__body">
          <p>
            Automancer is founded and run by Waseem Ilyas — an engineer who got tired of watching good
            small businesses drown in admin that a machine could do in seconds.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before Automancer, he spun out a SaaS company from the ground up — building and operating a
            live product business, not just advising on one. That's the difference you'll feel working with
            him: he's shipped real software that real people pay for and depend on, and he brings that same
            standard to your project. Nothing here is a slide deck. It's built, monitored, backed up and running.
          </p>
          <p>
            He works with clients across social care, manufacturing, professional services and travel —
            from a ~600-person care provider's whole digital transformation to a one-page website for a
            brand-new travel agency. Same care, whatever the size.
          </p>
          <p>
            When you work with Automancer, you work with Waseem. He reads your enquiry himself. He scopes
            your project himself. And when there's a decision to make or a call to take, that's him too.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How we work -->
  <section class="section on-near">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-head__top">
          <p class="eyebrow">How we do things</p>
          <span class="section-head__log">// rules_kept: 5/5</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Five rules we actually keep.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="principles reveal-stagger">
        {principles.map((p, i) => (
          <div class="principle" data-spot>
            <span class="principle__n" aria-hidden="true">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
            <h3>{p.name}</h3>
            <p>{p.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section on-dark cta hatch">
    <div class="cta__glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 class="cta__head">Want a business that runs a bit more like ours?</h2>
      <p class="cta__body">
        Start with an Audit and we'll show you exactly where AI and automation would earn their keep in
        your business — with real numbers and a plain plan.
      </p>
      <div class="cta__ctas">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn"><span>Book an Audit — from £450</span></a>
        <a href="/work" class="btn btn--ghost"><span>See the work</span><span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
